subSubSection.paragraph:
Front, mesoscutum, scutellum and metanotum with moderate micropuntation and shallow mesopunctation (
Fig. 27
); ventral region of mesopleuron with distinct punctures; clypeus with short golden bristles, except on ventral margin, which has elongated bristles; eyes with minute and sparse bristles; body almost completely with short bristles; propodeum with long and sparse bristles.

Distribution. Argentina : Misiones ; Bolivia : Beni , * La Paz ; Brazil : * Amapá , * Acre , * Amazonas , Bahia , *D. F., Espirito Santo , Goiás , Maranhão , Mato Grosso , Minas Gerais , Pará , Rio de Janeiro , * Rondônia , Santa Catarina , São Paulo ; Colombia : * Amazonas , * Caqueta , Magdalena , * Putumayo ; Ecuador : Napo ;
French Guiana
; Guyana ;
Paraguay
; Peru : Huánuco , Junín , Loreto , Cerro de Pasco ; Surinam , Venezuela .
